Difference
==========
---
Key Differences: RC vs RS

Feature	        | ReplicationController (RC)	                      | ReplicaSet (RS)
Purpose	        | Ensures a fixed number of running pods	           | Same as RC but more powerful
Label Matching	 | Supports only exact match (matchLabels)	         |Supports both exact match & expressions (matchLabels + matchExpressions)
Recommended?	   | ❌ Deprecated (not recommended)	                 | ✅ Preferred for standalone pod replication (but Deployment is better)
Updates Support	| ❌ No built-in rolling updates	                  | ❌ No built-in updates (use Deployments instead)
Best Use Case	  | Legacy applications in older Kubernetes versions	| When you need replication without Deployment

📌 Deployment uses ReplicaSet internally, so you should use Deployments instead of RS or RC!

---

=> ReplicaSet use Set-Based selectors which gives more flexibility while replication controllers use Equity-Based selectors.
ReplicaSets example

URL => https://blog.learncodeonline.in/kubernetes-core-concepts-replicasets-and-replication-controllers

ReplicaSets supports Set-Based selectors. Three type of operators used in set-based selectors are -->
  1. in
  2. notin
  3. exists

ReplicationController supports equality based selectors. Three type of operators used in equality based selectors are -->
  1. =
  2. ==
  3. !=

